## 2. System Architecture (How It All Connects)

```mermaid
graph TD
    Browser["üåê Browser"] --> InertiaClient["Inertia.js (Client)"]
    InertiaClient --> VuePages["Vue 3 Pages"]
    VuePages --> AppLayout["AppLayout.vue (Sidebar + Navbar)"]
    
    Browser --> LaravelRouter["Laravel Router (web.php)"]
    LaravelRouter --> Middleware["Middleware (Auth, Permission)"]
    Middleware --> Controllers["Controllers (25 total)"]
    Controllers --> Models["Eloquent Models (45 total)"]
    Models --> MySQL["MySQL Database (cattlesystem)"]
    
    Controllers --> InertiaServer["Inertia::render()"]
    InertiaServer --> VuePages
```

### Key Architecture Concepts:

| Concept | What It Means |
|---------|--------------|
| **MVC Pattern** | Model (data) ‚Üí Controller (logic) ‚Üí View (Vue pages) |
| **Inertia.js** | Instead of building REST APIs, controllers return `Inertia::render('PageName', data)` which directly sends data to Vue components. No need for axios/fetch calls for page loads. |
| **Eloquent ORM** | Each database table has a PHP Model class. You interact with the DB using PHP objects instead of raw SQL. |
| **Middleware** | Code that runs *before* your controller. Used for checking if user is logged in (`auth`) and checking permissions (`permission:ModuleName`). |

