## 4. All Modules Explained (The Big Picture)

### üêÆ Module 1: Cattle Management
**What it does:** Register, track, and manage individual cattle.

**Key data fields:** Tag No, LCC Running Number, Category, Breed, Coat Colour, Birth Date, Gender, Weight Milestones (receival, weaning, yearling), Dam/Sire Genealogy, Status, Location (block/phase).

**Features:**
- Full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
- Custom fields (dynamic fields admins can add)
- Export to Excel
- Profile picture upload
- Relationships to treatments, movements, and breeding records

**Route:** `/cattle` ‚Üí `CattleController`

---

### üçº Module 2: Calving (Birth Records)
**What it does:** Records when a calf is born ‚Äî who the mother/father is, condition, treatments given.

**Endorsement Workflow:**  
`Issued ‚Üí Verified ‚Üí Checked ‚Üí Witnessed ‚Üí Approved`

Each step is done by a different role (configurable via Access Control Matrix). The system tracks who signed off at each step with name, date, and digital signature.

**Key data:** Company info, calf tag, calving date, sex (MC/FC), dam/sire details, herd, location, worker name.

**Features:**
- LCC Document download (official birth certificate)
- Endorsement document upload/download at each step
- Bulk delete
- Export records
- Filter by month and operating unit

**Route:** `/calving` ‚Üí `CalvingController`

---

### üìã Module 3: Calving Checklist
**What it does:** A monthly checklist form for calving records ‚Äî ensures all steps are properly documented.

**Same workflow:** Issued ‚Üí Verified ‚Üí Checked ‚Üí Witnessed ‚Üí Approved

**Extra features:**
- Batch endorsement (sign off on multiple records at once)
- Export report
- Monthly reporting

**Route:** `/calving-checklist` ‚Üí `CalvingChecklistController`

---

### üíÄ Module 4: Mortality (Death Records)
**What it does:** Records cattle deaths ‚Äî what happened, when, where, cause of death.

**Workflow:**  
`Issued ‚Üí Verified ‚Üí Checked ‚Üí Witness ‚Üí Approved`

**Post-Mortem Examination:** After recording a death, a PM examination form can be filled in with detailed findings.

**Key data:** Cattle ID, LMC number, category, location, herd, block, death date, time, cause, treatment attempted.

**Features:**
- PM Examination module (detailed post-mortem form)
- Pending approvals dashboard
- Completed cases view
- Custom fields
- Endorsement document workflow with upload/download
- Mark as completed

**Route:** `/mortality` ‚Üí `MortalityController`

---

### üíä Module 5: Health & Treatment
**What it does:** Records medical treatments given to cattle ‚Äî symptoms, treatment applied, medication, dosage.

**Workflow:**  
`Prepared ‚Üí Checked ‚Üí Approved`

**Key data:** Treatment number, cattle tag, category, operating unit, date, symptoms, treatment code, dosage, medication, follow-up scheduling.

**Features:**
- Monthly workflow (batch endorsement by month/year/unit)
- Treatment codes management (predefined treatment categories)
- Veterinary contact management
- Endorsement document upload/download
- Export report
- Reopen completed records

**Route:** `/health/treatment` ‚Üí `HealthTreatmentController`

---

### üöö Module 6: Transfer (Cattle Movement Between Locations)
**What it does:** Manages official transfer documents when cattle move between estates/locations.

**3 Document Types:**
| Type | Full Name | Purpose |
|------|-----------|---------|
| **CTV** | Cattle Transfer Voucher | Moving cattle out |
| **Receival** | Receival Document | Receiving cattle in |
| **SIV** | Sales Invoice Voucher | Selling cattle |

**Workflow (8 steps!):**  
`Issued ‚Üí Approved ‚Üí Transported ‚Üí Witness Transit ‚Üí Verified Transit ‚Üí Witness Receive ‚Üí Received ‚Üí Completed`

**Key data:** Document number, from/to location, date, vehicle number, driver details, livestock list.

**Route:** `/transfer` ‚Üí `TransferController`

---

### üåø Module 7: Pasture & Grazing
**What it does:** Manages the physical land structure ‚Äî estates, herds, blocks, and grazing phases.

**Hierarchy:** `Estate ‚Üí Herd ‚Üí Block ‚Üí Phase`

**Features:**
- Pasture management (operating units with herds and blocks)
- Data Input page for grazing data
- Herd Cards (detailed estate-level view with grazing details)

**Routes:**
- `/pasture/all` ‚Üí Pasture management
- `/data-input` ‚Üí Grazing data input
- `/herd-cards` ‚Üí Herd card views

---

### üçΩÔ∏è Module 8: Feeding
**What it does:** Records daily feeding activities for cattle herds.

**Features:**
- Feeding record CRUD
- Schedule view
- PDF export

**Route:** `/feeding` ‚Üí `FeedingController`

