## 5. User & Permission System

### User Model:
- Fields: name, email, password, **role**, **status**, last_login_at
- Roles are just strings (e.g., "Admin", "Livestock", "Supervisor", "Manager")
- **Admins bypass all permission checks**

### Permission System (3 layers):

| Layer | What it controls |
|-------|-----------------|
| **Module Permissions** | Per-user access to modules: `no-access`, `view`, `create`, `edit`, `full`, `approve` |
| **Field-Level Permissions** | Control which fields specific users can see/edit |
| **Workflow Assignments** | Which users are assigned to each endorsement step |

### How permissions work:
1. Middleware `CheckModulePermission` runs before controller
2. Checks [permissions](file:///c:/wamp64/www/cattle-project/app/Models/User.php#55-62) table: does this user have access to this module?
3. Admins always pass (`role === 'admin'`)
4. Each module has configurable workflow assignments (who can issue, verify, check, witness, approve)

### Access Control Matrix:
A single page (`/access-control`) where admins set all permissions for all users across all modules. Also configures workflow assignments for Treatment, Calving, and Transfer modules.

---

## 6. Endorsement Workflow Pattern (IMPORTANT ‚Äî Used Everywhere!)

This is the **core pattern** used across Mortality, Health, Calving, Calving Checklist, and Transfer modules:

```
‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
‚îÇ                 ENDORSEMENT WORKFLOW                         ‚îÇ
‚îÇ                                                              ‚îÇ
‚îÇ  1. Record Created (status: pending)                         ‚îÇ
‚îÇ          ‚Üì                                                   ‚îÇ
‚îÇ  2. Step-by-step approval by assigned users                  ‚îÇ
‚îÇ     Each step: user signs ‚Üí uploads endorsement doc          ‚îÇ
‚îÇ          ‚Üì                                                   ‚îÇ
‚îÇ  3. Final step reached ‚Üí status: approved/completed          ‚îÇ
‚îÇ                                                              ‚îÇ
‚îÇ  At any step: can be REJECTED with reason                    ‚îÇ
‚îÇ  After completion: admin can REOPEN if needed                ‚îÇ
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò
```

**Technical implementation:**
- Each record has `current_step`, `endorsement_step` (integer), `endorsement_documents` (JSON), and `status`
- `endorsement_documents` stores uploaded file paths for each step
- Controller methods: `issue()`, `verify()`, `witness()`, `approve()`, `reject()`, `markAsCompleted()`, `reopen()`
- PDF endorsement forms can be generated and downloaded

