## 8. Audit Logging
Every important action is logged in the `audit_logs` table. The Dashboard shows recent activities with:
- Who did it (user)
- What module (cattle, mortality, etc.)
- What action (created, updated, approved, etc.)
- Details of the change

---

## 9. Key Technical Decisions to Mention

| Decision | Why |
|----------|-----|
| **Inertia.js instead of REST API** | Faster development ‚Äî no need to build separate API endpoints. Controllers directly pass data to Vue components. |
| **Endorsement workflow as a reusable pattern** | Same approval flow used across 5 modules ‚Äî reduces code duplication. |
| **Role-based + Module-based permissions** | Flexible ‚Äî admins can grant different access levels per user per module. |
| **Custom fields system** | Allows adding new data fields without modifying the database schema (stored as JSON or in separate custom_fields table). |
| **MySQL on WAMP** | Simple local development setup, easy to deploy. |
| **DomPDF + TCPDF** | Generate official documents (LCC certificates, endorsement forms) as downloadable PDFs. |
| **PhpSpreadsheet** | Export data to Excel for reporting. |

---

## 10. Quick Interview Cheat Sheet

### "What does your system do?"
> "It's a **Cattle Management System** for livestock estates. It digitizes the entire lifecycle of cattle ‚Äî from **birth (calving)** to **health treatments**, **transfers between locations**, and **mortality recording**. Every critical record goes through a multi-step **endorsement workflow** where different stakeholders (livestock officers, supervisors, managers, security) must sign off."

### "What tech stack did you use?"
> "**Laravel 12** backend, **Vue 3** frontend with **Inertia.js** as the bridge, **MySQL** database, styled with **Tailwind CSS**, and built with **Vite**."

### "What's the most complex part?"
> "The **endorsement workflow system** ‚Äî it supports multi-step approval (up to 8 steps for transfers), with document upload/download at each step, digital signatures, rejection with reasons, and the ability for admins to reopen completed records."

### "How do you handle permissions?"
> "Three-layer system: **module-level permissions** (what modules can you access), **field-level permissions** (what fields can you see), and **workflow assignments** (who is assigned to approve at each step). Admins configure everything through an **Access Control Matrix** page."

### "How many modules does it have?"
> "**11 main modules**: Cattle Management, Calving Records, Calving Checklists, Mortality & Post-Mortem, Health Treatment, Transfer Documents (CTV/SIV/Receival), Pasture & Grazing, Feeding, Inventory, Driver Management, and Task Management ‚Äî plus admin modules for User Management, Permissions, and Audit Logs."

---

